  <Docs>
    <summary>Represents a four-byte ASCII tag used to identify OpenType font tables, variation axes, and other named resources.</summary>
    <remarks>
      <format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFourByteTag` represents a 32-bit identifier composed of four ASCII characters. Four-byte tags are used throughout OpenType and Skia to identify font tables (e.g., `"head"`, `"hhea"`), variation axes (e.g., `"wght"`, `"ital"`), and other named resources.

You can construct a tag from a string using the `Parse` method, from individual characters using the four-character constructor, or from a raw `uint` value. An implicit conversion from `uint` is also available.

This is a value type that does not require disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
// Parse from a string
var wghtTag = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wght");

// Construct from characters
var italTag = new SKFourByteTag('i', 't', 'a', 'l');

// Use as a uint
uint raw = wghtTag;
```
]]></format>
    </remarks>
  </Docs>
